						<div class="postbody">Looks like you're only showing Coarse Y (tile number).  Fine Y (pixel number) would give more detail, but this should be good enough!<br /><br />Take a look here:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">Scanline 15: loopy Y = 1, loopy H = 0<br />Scanline 16: loopy Y = 2, loopy H = 0<br />...<br />Scanline 23: loopy Y = 2, loopy H = 0<br />Scanline 24: loopy Y = 3, loopy H = 0<br /></div><br /><br />Coarse Y=2 for exactly 8 scanlines, which is what I would expect.<br /><br />Now take a look at Y=3 (where the split occurs):<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">Scanline 23: loopy Y = 2, loopy H = 0<br />Scanline 24: loopy Y = 3, loopy H = 0<br />... split occurs in here ...<br />Scanline 38: loopy Y = 3, loopy H = 0<br />Scanline 39: loopy Y = 4, loopy H = 0<br /></div><br /><br />Y=3 for 15 scanlines!!!<br /><br />Note that the game is only writing to $2005, and not to $2006... and with that mechanism alone it is impossible to change the Y scroll.<br /><br />So the problem must be in the way you're handling $2005 writes.  Can you post that code here?  It looks like you are resetting fine Y scroll or something.</div>

